          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141195681" href="/book/show/14800047-waiting-period">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39791779-tim?shelf=philosophical">philosophical</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39791779-tim?shelf=literature-english">literature-english</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39791779-tim?shelf=characters">characters</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2278520302" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12913615455790271206">In his very last novel Selby once again explores the depths and abysses of the human mind. Although uncompromising and honest, this read proved way tougher than his masterpiece <i>Requiem for a Dream</i>. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


