<div id="review_584570113" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/584570113" />
    <a title="Will" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18273035-will"><img alt="Will" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/584570113?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Will" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Will" href="/user/show/18273035-will">Will</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer584570113" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12093757752538062160">The one occasion so far when Selby&apos;s method of narration does not work. This book would need to step a little outside the narrator&apos;s head and into other perspectives (eg, when he attempts to buy the gun, you&apos;d need to see him from the gunshop dealer&apos;s point of view, get a physical description of this twitchy paranoid customer, etc, rather than just dialogue and stream of consciousness.) Also there seemed a lack of specifics in his dislike of the world, not enough going over specific incidents in</span>
  <span id="freeText12093757752538062160" style="display:none">The one occasion so far when Selby's method of narration does not work. This book would need to step a little outside the narrator's head and into other perspectives (eg, when he attempts to buy the gun, you'd need to see him from the gunshop dealer's point of view, get a physical description of this twitchy paranoid customer, etc, rather than just dialogue and stream of consciousness.) Also there seemed a lack of specifics in his dislike of the world, not enough going over specific incidents in the past, those which brought him to his current state of insanity. All too general and vague. Didn't work on this occasion, but hats off to the author for experimenting.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12093757752538062160" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


